==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disparate
<hw>Dis"pa*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>disparatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>disparare</ets> to part, separate;
<ets>dis-</ets> + <ets>parare</ets> to make ready, prepare.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Unequal; dissimilar; separate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Connecting <qex>disparate</qex> thoughts, purely by means of
resemblances in the words expressing them.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Logic)</fld> <def>Pertaining to two coordinate
species or divisions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disparates</ent>⟦br⟧
